english:
  title: Another
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your sacred instructions are steadfast and true—fostering compassion and succor with unwavering devotion. Your imperial grace spreads boundless, stirring such profound gratitude that though my bones should turn to dust, I could never repay it. Trembling in awe, I know not where to turn.

    In quiet reflection, I consider how these minor officials formed dark alliances with corrupt factions, brazenly pursuing deceitful schemes. They defied the luminous edicts you had sent down repeatedly, abandoning the ancestral lands where their families had dwelt for generations. They seduced the innocent into flight and dared to gather with the Jurchens. Fearing that frontier troubles might kindle anew, I laid bare my humble heart and humbly petitioned you—never imagining your celestial gaze would penetrate so deeply.

    Yet you have issued a warm edict and proclaimed it far and wide. Recognizing my failures in governing these distant peoples, you offered stern guidance, commanding them to return and resettle in their rightful occupations, thus dispelling all suspicion. And when I submitted my pleas again and again, you graciously heeded them all—a singular mercy rarely granted across the ages.

    This flows from a compassion exceeding that of parents themselves, a virtue harmonizing with heaven and earth. You regard the four seas as one household and shelter all the people as cherished children. Through such boundless kindness, our realm has received your immense favor.

    I vow to steadfastly strengthen these eastern lands, to discharge my duties as vassal with ever greater care, and to raise ceaseless prayers of gratitude, pouring forth all the sincerity of my devoted heart.
